# Seek Medical Attention

Stop wearing your contact lenses and seek advice from a qualified eye care professional immediately if you experience symptoms such as:

* Severe or increasing eye pain
* Sudden vision loss or blurred vision
* Significant redness
* Light sensitivity
* Persistent discharge
* Eye injury
* Any symptom that causes concern

If you believe you are experiencing a medical emergency, seek immediate medical attention or contact your local emergency services.

